  <h_narrative_case_summary>
    <h_1_case_narrative><value>A 22-year-old female patient with a history of hypertension and type 2 diabetes presented with sudden onset dizziness, weakness, and palpitations approximately 30 minutes after taking Metformin 500mg. She also reported difficulty breathing. Blood glucose was critically elevated at 550 mg/dL. ECG showed ST-segment elevation in V1-V4. The patient was admitted to the ICU. Metformin was withdrawn immediately. Symptoms resolved after 2 days of treatment. The patient was discharged in stable condition on day 5.</value></h_1_case_narrative>
    <h_2_reporter_comments><value>Possible hypersensitivity reaction to Metformin. Causality assessment: probable.</value></h_2_reporter_comments>
    <h_4_sender_comments><value>Report reviewed and confirmed by pharmacovigilance department. Follow-up requested.</value></h_4_sender_comments>
  </h_narrative_case_summary>
